{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a8f7c9e3-fund-transfer-api-demo",
    "name": "Fund Transfer API (demo)",
    "description": "## Fund Transfer API — Postman demo\n\n**Important:** **`jwtToken`** must be the **signed JWT string** printed by **`php bin/console app:security:issue-token SOME_SUB`** — NOT the 32-character server secret.\nThe secret belongs only in **`.env.local`** as **`JWT_SECRET_KEY`**.\n\n1. Run the app (`php -S 127.0.0.1:8000 -t public` or Symfony CLI).\n2. Migrate and seed demo accounts (`doctrine:migrations:migrate`, `app:seed-demo-accounts`).\n3. Set variables **fromAccountId** and **toAccountId** from the seed output.\n4. Use **GET /api/me** to see **`subject`** (`anonymous` vs JWT `sub`). Set **`PUBLIC_API_ALLOW_ANONYMOUS=0`** to require a token on protected routes.\n\nOptional: **apiKey** for `X-API-Key`.\n\nFile: `postman/Fund-Transfer-API.demo.postman_collection.json`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000" },
    { "key": "fromAccountId", "value": "REPLACE_AFTER_SEED_DEMO_ACCOUNTS_FROM_UUID" },
    { "key": "toAccountId", "value": "REPLACE_AFTER_SEED_DEMO_ACCOUNTS_TO_UUID" },
    { "key": "jwtToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "apiKey", "value": "" },
    { "key": "idempotencyDemoKey", "value": "postman-demo-idem-001" },
    { "key": "idempotencyConflictKey", "value": "postman-demo-conflict-001" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Anonymous / dev (no Bearer)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health",
            "description": "Liveness probe — returns JSON with `status: ok`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Who am I (GET /api/me)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/me",
            "description": "With default **PUBLIC_API_ALLOW_ANONYMOUS=1**, expect **`{\"subject\":\"anonymous\",...}`** even with no Bearer. After you mint a JWT, this folder does not auto-send it — use **With JWT Bearer → Who am I** to see your **`sub`**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get account balance",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/accounts/{{fromAccountId}}",
            "description": "Reads `balanceMinor` (string integer minor units)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create transfer",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fromAccountId\": \"{{fromAccountId}}\",\n  \"toAccountId\": \"{{toAccountId}}\",\n  \"amountMinor\": \"500\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transfers",
            "description": "**201** Created with `transferId`, `fromAccountId`, `toAccountId`, `amountMinor`, `createdAt`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create transfer (idempotent replay)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "{{idempotencyDemoKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fromAccountId\": \"{{fromAccountId}}\",\n  \"toAccountId\": \"{{toAccountId}}\",\n  \"amountMinor\": \"50\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transfers",
            "description": "Run **twice** with the **same** body and key — second call returns the **same** `transferId` (no double debit). Uses variable `idempotencyDemoKey`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create transfer — prime Idempotency-Key conflict demo (amount 1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "{{idempotencyConflictKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fromAccountId\": \"{{fromAccountId}}\",\n  \"toAccountId\": \"{{toAccountId}}\",\n  \"amountMinor\": \"1\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transfers",
            "description": "Run **once** before the next request. Uses **idempotencyConflictKey**. Expect **201**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create transfer — Idempotency-Key reused with DIFFERENT body (409)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "{{idempotencyConflictKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fromAccountId\": \"{{fromAccountId}}\",\n  \"toAccountId\": \"{{toAccountId}}\",\n  \"amountMinor\": \"999\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transfers",
            "description": "Run **after** the prime request. Same **idempotencyConflictKey** but larger amount → **409 Conflict**. Change variable **idempotencyConflictKey** to repeat this flow."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Insufficient funds example",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fromAccountId\": \"{{fromAccountId}}\",\n  \"toAccountId\": \"{{toAccountId}}\",\n  \"amountMinor\": \"999999999999999\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transfers",
            "description": "**422** when amount exceeds sender balance."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Validation error (same account)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fromAccountId\": \"{{fromAccountId}}\",\n  \"toAccountId\": \"{{fromAccountId}}\",\n  \"amountMinor\": \"1\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transfers",
            "description": "**400** — from and to must differ."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "With JWT Bearer",
      "auth": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "bearer": [
          {
            "key": "token",
            "value": "{{jwtToken}}",
            "type": "string"
          }
        ]
      },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health (still public)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health",
            "description": "Inherited JWT disabled — health stays public."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Who am I (JWT sub)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/me",
            "description": "Set **jwtToken** to the output of **`app:security:issue-token my-demo-sub`**. Expect **`subject\": \"my-demo-sub\"`** (your `sub` claim). Leave **jwtToken** empty and set **PUBLIC_API_ALLOW_ANONYMOUS=0** to get **401**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get account balance",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/accounts/{{fromAccountId}}",
            "description": "Requires valid JWT when **`JWT_SECRET_KEY`** is set and **`PUBLIC_API_ALLOW_ANONYMOUS=0`**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create transfer",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fromAccountId\": \"{{fromAccountId}}\",\n  \"toAccountId\": \"{{toAccountId}}\",\n  \"amountMinor\": \"100\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transfers",
            "description": "Idempotency owner is scoped to JWT **`sub`** — two different subjects may reuse the same visible `Idempotency-Key`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "With X-API-Key (no Bearer)",
      "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Who am I (API key client)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "{{apiKey}}" }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/me",
            "description": "Set **`apiKey`** (collection Variables) to the **exact** same string as server **`API_KEY`** in `.env.local`. Expect **`subject\": \"api-key-client\"** and **200**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get account balance",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "{{apiKey}}" }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/accounts/{{fromAccountId}}",
            "description": "Set **`apiKey`** in collection variables when `API_KEY` is configured."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create transfer",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "{{apiKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fromAccountId\": \"{{fromAccountId}}\",\n  \"toAccountId\": \"{{toAccountId}}\",\n  \"amountMinor\": \"25\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/transfers",
            "description": "Alternative to JWT."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
